## Coding Standards

### Feature-Sliced Design
- See `fsd.mdc` for full architecture rules.

### Keep it SOLID
- Keep state management separated from ui.
- Single Responsibility: one concern per file.
- Depend on abstractions (types), not concretions.

### Strict TypeScript
- No `any` or `unknown` types; explicit types only.
- Every function parameter and return type must be annotated.
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for object shapes.

### Absolute Imports
- Always use `@/` prefix for imports from `src/`.
- Alphabetical import ordering: external packages first, then `@/` imports by layer.

### Array Methods
- Prefer JavaScript array methods (`map`, `filter`, `forEach`, `reduce`, `find`, `some`, `every`) over `for` loops.

### Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind utility classes for all styling.
- Shared UI atoms live in `@/shared/ui/`.
